{#
  Index page for one bucket of OFAC SDN designations
  (/sanctions/individuals, /sanctions/entities, /sanctions/vessels,
  /sanctions/aircraft).

  Server-rendered alphabetical directory — every name is a real,
  crawlable link out to its own profile page. Google + Bing crawlers
  follow these out of the index, so this page is the structural
  backbone that gets all 410 children indexed.

  Also serves humans browsing by surname. We group individuals by first
  letter to keep the page scannable on mobile; entities/vessels/aircraft
  fall into the same A-Z layout.
#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container-wide">
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/sanctions-tracker">OFAC Venezuela Sanctions</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <strong>{{ bucket|capitalize }}</strong>
  </nav>

  <article>
    <header>
      <h1>OFAC Venezuela SDN — {{ bucket|capitalize }} ({{ profiles|length }} active)</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Every {{ singular }} currently on the US Treasury OFAC SDN list under
        Venezuela-related sanctions programs. Each entry links to a full
        profile with biographical data, linked entities, and recent news.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">
        <span><strong>Source:</strong> US Treasury OFAC SDN List</span>
        <span><strong>Refreshed:</strong> twice daily (10am &amp; 5pm Medellín)</span>
        <span><strong>Programs covered:</strong> VENEZUELA, EO 13692, EO 13850, EO 13884</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="body">
      <p>
        Browse alphabetically below, or use these one-click filters to jump to a
        specific category:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/individuals"><strong>Individuals</strong></a> ({{ stats.individuals }}) — natural persons designated for human-rights, corruption, or government-of-Venezuela activities.</li>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/entities"><strong>Entities</strong></a> ({{ stats.entities }}) — companies, ministries, holding vehicles, and shell organisations.</li>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/vessels"><strong>Vessels</strong></a> ({{ stats.vessels }}) — ships blocked under Venezuela-related programs.</li>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/aircraft"><strong>Aircraft</strong></a> ({{ stats.aircraft }}) — planes blocked under Venezuela-related programs.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>All {{ bucket }} (A–Z)</h2>
      {% if grouped %}
      {% for letter, items in grouped %}
      <h3 id="{{ letter }}">{{ letter }}</h3>
      <ul class="related">
        {% for p in items %}
        <li>
          <a href="{{ p.url_path }}">{{ p.display_name }}</a>
          <small>— {{ p.program }}{% if p.parsed.dob %} · DOB {{ p.parsed.dob }}{% elif p.parsed.imo %} · IMO {{ p.parsed.imo }}{% elif p.parsed.aircraft_tail %} · Tail {{ p.parsed.aircraft_tail }}{% endif %}</small>
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
      {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
      <p>No designations are currently indexed in this category.</p>
      {% endif %}

      <h2>Why these pages exist</h2>
      <p>
        Each {{ singular }} on this list has its own dedicated profile page so that
        compliance, M&amp;A, and journalist research workflows can link directly to
        a permanent URL with the SDN entry's biographical data, OFAC source link,
        and any related news mentions. We update from OFAC's primary feed twice
        daily; for live, transactional screening, always cross-check with
        <a href="https://sanctions-search.ofac.treasury.gov/" rel="nofollow">OFAC's official Sanctions Search</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
{% endblock %}
